            "text": "{\n  \"id\": \"resp_06c4481c58180f0e0069d6453f0b90819ba00cf0f55e30c046\",\n  \"object\": \"response\",\n  \"created_at\": 1775650111,\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"background\": false,\n  \"billing\": {\n    \"payer\": \"openai\"\n  },\n  \"completed_at\": 1775650114,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"frequency_penalty\": 0.0,\n  \"incomplete_details\": null,\n  \"instructions\": null,\n  \"max_output_tokens\": 500,\n  \"max_tool_calls\": null,\n  \"model\": \"o4-mini-2025-04-16\",\n  \"output\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rs_06c4481c58180f0e0069d6453f67cc819bbc16ea2eb4e6fab2\",\n      \"type\": \"reasoning\",\n      \"summary\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"summary_text\",\n          \"text\": \"**Counting letters in strawberry**\\n\\nThe user wants to know how many times the letter \\\"r\\\" appears in \\\"strawberry.\\\" I see the letters: s, t, r, a, w, b, e, r, r, y. The letter \\\"r\\\" shows up at positions 3, 8, and 9. So, there are three \\\"r's\\\" in total. The word \\\"strawberry\\\" is ten letters long, which I have confirmed. To wrap it up, the answer is definitely three!\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"msg_06c4481c58180f0e0069d64542621c819b8d4da9fc35c8af0b\",\n      \"type\": \"message\",\n      \"status\": \"completed\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"output_text\",\n          \"annotations\": [],\n          \"logprobs\": [],\n          \"text\": \"The word \\u201cstrawberry\\u201d contains three \\u201cr\\u201d letters.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"role\": \"assistant\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"parallel_tool_calls\": true,\n  \"presence_penalty\": 0.0,\n  \"previous_response_id\": null,\n  \"prompt_cache_key\": null,\n  \"prompt_cache_retention\": null,\n  \"reasoning\": {\n    \"effort\": \"low\",\n    \"summary\": \"detailed\"\n  },\n  \"safety_identifier\": null,\n  \"service_tier\": \"default\",\n  \"store\": true,\n  \"temperature\": 1.0,\n  \"text\": {\n    \"format\": {\n      